{{Infobox football biography |name = Demeaco Duhaney |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Demeaco Duhaney<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/844127|title=2018/19 Premier League squads confirmed|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=27 February 2019|publisher=Premier League}}</ref> |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|10|13|df=y}}<ref name = "SW">{{soccerway|demeaco-duhaney/420442/|accessdate=4 Janary 2019}}</ref> |birth_place = |height = 1.80m<ref name = "SW"/> |position = [[Defender (association football)|Right back]] |currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] |clubnumber = 38 |youthyears1 = 2006–2018 |youthclubs1 = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] |youthyears2 = 2018–2019 |youthclubs2 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] |years1 = 2019– |clubs1 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] |caps1 = 1 |goals1 = 0 |nationalyears1 = |nationalteam1 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] |nationalcaps1 = |nationalgoals1 = |club-update = 09:50, 27 February 2019 (UTC) |ntupdate = 12:24, 2 January 2019 (UTC) }} '''Demeaco Duhaney''' (born 13 October 1998) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], as a [[Defender (association football)|right back]].
==Club career== Duhaney joined [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] at the age of 5.<ref name = "debut"/> He made three appearances for the Under-21s in the [[EFL Trophy]] during the 2017–18 season.<ref>{{soccerbase season|105834|2017|accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref>
He signed for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] in August 2018.<ref name = "HT">{{cite web|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2018/august/signing-eng-u20-defender-demeaco-duhaney/|title=SIGNING: ENG U20 DEFENDER DEMEACO DUHANEY|date=17 August 2018|accessdate=2 January 2019|publisher=Huddersfield Town A.F.C.}}</ref> Due to the suspension of regular right-back [[Tommy Smith (footballer, born 1992)|Tommy Smith]], Duhaney made his senior debut on 26 February 2019, in a 1–0 home [[Premier League]] victory against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref name = "debut">{{cite web|url=https://www.examinerlive.co.uk/sport/football/jan-siewert-explains-picked-manchester-15892598|title=Jan Siewert explains why he picked Manchester City product Demeaco Duhaney for Huddersfield Town debut against Wolves|date=27 February 2019|accessdate=27 February 2019|author=Mel Booth|publisher=Huddersfield Examiner}}</ref><ref>{{soccerbase season|105834|2018|accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref> He was substituted at half-time due to potential injury problems, and his performance in the game was praised by mangager [[Jan Siewert]].<ref name = "debut"/>
==International career== He has represented England at international youth levels, including [[England national under-20 football team|under-20]].<ref name = "HT"/>
